*seahorse-0.6.0 (6 Jan 2003)

	15 Jan 2003; Jean Schurger <yshark@schurger.org>
	Makefine.am: add MAINTAINERS
	seahorse.spec.in: merge my original spec file with the Yanko Kaneti one (see %changelog) 

	13 Jan 2003; Jacob Perkins <jap1@users.sourceforge.net>

	Removed unecessary translation macros from objects

	10 Jan 2003; Jacob Perkins <jap1@users.sourceforge.net>
	
	Added hash table to key-widget to ensure only one dialog of each type per key, modified wins & dialogs appropriately
	Signatures is now a widget, not a key-widget; removed option to show key properties; shows uid & keyid of signer
	Added SeahorseWidget::new_allow_multiple to accomodate needs of Signatures
	Changed 'Algorithm' to 'Type' in key manager store
	Changed context to GtkObject for destroy signal, re-added SeahorseContext::destroy
	Widgets now listen to context's destroy signal, destroying self when called so context & keys always finalized

	9 Jan 2003; Jacob Perkins <jap1@users.sourceforge.net>
	
	Moved SeahorseKeyType & SeahorseKeyLength to ops-key
	Removed SeahorseContext::destroy since only unrefs
	Ref counting code audit, minor changes to following:
		key, context, widget, key-widget, key-menu, key-menu-item, recipients
	Added delete_event to all dialogs so destroyed properly
	Added hash table to widget in order to ensure only one dialog of each type, modified wins & dialogs appropriately

	7 Jan 2003; Jacob Perkins <jap1@users.sourceforge.net>
	
	Changed key properties so primary expiration date widget is not a date editor for key's without secret part
	Made key properties display code more efficient with ::do_stats.
	Added some checks in passphrase to stop segfaults
	Removed key-properties::key_changed
	Remove extra table rows in key properties.

	6 Jan 2003; Jacob Perkins <jap1@users.sourceforge.net>
	
	Fixed context bug #658788
	Added context methods context::set_ascii_armor, set_text_mode, set_signer, get_signer
	Moved gconf preferences handling to context
	Modified preferences appropriately
	Key-menu will no longer add key's without secret if secret is needed
	Moved seahorse.schemas to seahorse.schemas.in and modified auto* files so install schemas correctly
	De-widgetized signatures, signature can be verified without showing signing key (for plugins).

*seahorse-0.4.4 (16 Dec 2002)

	20 Dec 2002; Jacob Perkins <jap1@users.sourceforge.net>
	
	Removed default_key schema, preferences now only uses default_key_id pref.
	Reworked preferences appropriately

	19 Dec 2002; Jacob Perkins <jap1@users.sourceforge.net>
	
	Preferences now only shows keys with a secret key

	18 Dec 2002; Jacob Perkins <jap1@users.sourceforge.net>
	
	Added seahorse-key::get_userid to get utf8 valid ids
	Removed seahorse-key::get_name in favor of ::get_userid
	Added stubs for changing a key's passphrase
	Added passphrase changing operation: needs some usability work due to gpgme's status line
	Hide key-properties edit menu if don't have secret key
	
	17 Dec 2002; Jacob Perkins <jap1@users.sourceforge.net>
	
	Completed key-store transition
	Desensitize main window while an operation (generate) is in progress
	Added stubs for key server ops in seahorse-ops-key::export_server & ::import_server
	Added key count & bad file to import status
	
	16 Dec 2002; Jacob Perkins <jap1@users.sourceforge.net>
	
	Made columns resizable
	Niced keyid
	Removed key-iters, functionality now internal to key-store & subclasses, modified other appropriately
	Lots of cleanup due to key-iter removal

